intent: >
  Bump Kamal's deploy_timeout from the 30s default to 120s so deploys stop
  failing before Rails has finished its ~60s cold boot on the prod droplet.

slice: "?/?"
kind: fix
behavior_change: none

reversibility: trivial

scope:
  declared: []
  actual:
    - config/deploy.yml
  drift: []

proof:
  tests_run: >-
    bin/dc ruby -r kamal -e 'puts Kamal::Configuration.create_from(config_file: Pathname.new("config/deploy.yml")).deploy_timeout'
  result: green
  failing: 0
  coverage_delta: "+0.0%"

tests:
  needed: "no"
  rationale: >
    Config-only change to a Kamal deploy parameter. Kamal parses the value
    (confirmed: Ruby reads it back as 120) and there is no application
    behavior to cover with a spec. Real verification is a successful deploy
    to prod, which only the next kamal deploy can prove. That's tracked
    under verification.manual and will be confirmed when the user deploys.

verification:
  tested:
    - "Kamal parses deploy_timeout: 120 (ruby -r kamal ... puts deploy_timeout -> 120)"
    - "bin/dc bin/kamal config loads without error after the edit"
  manual:
    - "Next deploy to production should clear the 30s cliff and complete -- pending"

assumptions:
  - "No active plan covers this slice -- ad-hoc hotfix for the failing 2026-04-15 02:29 UTC deploy"
  - "Rails cold boot on the 1vCPU/1GB droplet will fit inside 120s; observed ~60s until Puma begins listening, and /up is cheap once Puma is up"
  - "Kamal 2.11's deploy_timeout is passed to kamal-proxy as --deploy-timeout (verified in lib/kamal/cli/healthcheck/poller.rb and configuration/proxy.rb)"
  - "The 30s timeout in the failing deploy error message is the same deploy_timeout knob, not a separate proxy.healthcheck.timeout"

specifications:
  - "deploy_timeout is pinned in config/deploy.yml with inline rationale -- enforced in config, not just documented in an ADR"
  - "120s is the temporary floor until cold-boot is reduced (#27)"

deviations_from_plan: "no active plan -- ad-hoc hotfix for failing prod deploy"

trade_offs: >
  Treats the symptom, not the cause -- the ~60s cold boot is still there
  and #27 is the real fix. Accepted cost: failed deploys now take ~2
  minutes to surface instead of 30s, worse feedback latency on genuinely
  broken deploys. Accepted because right now no deploy can land at all.
  Alternative (reduce cold boot first) rejected as too much work for an
  unbreak-deploys slice; captured in #27 so it doesn't get lost.

self_review:
  consistency: >
    New top-level key + inline comment block matches the style of the
    WEB_CONCURRENCY=1 pin lower in the same file -- the why lives next to
    the value, no separate ADR-only documentation.
  metz: "N/A -- YAML config, no classes or methods."
  enforced_in_config: >
    Follows the project's enforce-constraints-in-config rule -- the
    constraint is load-bearing (deploys fail without it) so it lives in
    deploy.yml, not only in a doc or commit message.
  absolutist_tradeoff_language: >
    Comment and commit message frame this as an "accepted trade-off" with
    a named cost, per the project's no-absolutist-tradeoff-language rule.

confidence: high
reviewer_attention:
  - config/deploy.yml:8-22   # the deploy_timeout block + rationale -- check that the trade-off framing and 120s floor are the right call
